  "body" : "<p>I'm currently using the @Value Spring 3.1.x annotation like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Value(\"${stuff.value:}\")\nprivate String value;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This puts an empty String into the variable if the attribute is not present. I would like to have null as the default instead of an empty String. Of course I also want to avoid an error when the property stuff.value is not set.</p>\n"
